dismissalText.commentary: Tushar Imran run out (Otieno) 2 (13b 0x4 0x6) SR: 15.38

dismissalComment.html: What a comedy, Hassan defends to the off, Imran comes, Hassan hesitates, then tries to get back, Imran passes him, keeper diving underhands the ball into the stumps, both batsman are out of the crease, ball is picked up and returned to the bowler who flicks the bails off, again both are still standing in the middle of the wicket, TV umpire takes long to decide Imran is out with the keepers throw

commentTextItems.html: length ball outside the off stump, Hasan drives and again drives well, ball flashes away square of the wicket and a 6 wicket win for and a clean sweep for Bangladesh

commentPostTextItems.html: Joy for Bangladesh as they win their first away series
Thanks for spending your time with us, feel free to read the match reports and have a look at the pictures on www.cricinfo.com

commentTextItems.html: good length but down leg, Reza edges the ball as he drives again, inside edge squirts out to square leg area
line and length, Reza drives on the front foot, stand and deliver, he has had enough of the dabs and pushes, smashes that to long-off
good line and just short of a length, Hasan cuts it away behind square, gully chases and slides to pull it in, TV shows that is ok.
short ball, Hasan defends on the front foot, dabs to the off and brings the wrath of the crowd onto himself
wide outside the off stump, Hasan plays but misses the ball, huge appeal from bowler and keeper for a catch, but it was the bat hitting the ground, no contact with the ball
down the leg side, BANG, Reza lofted drives on the front foot, sends that miles high and long to deep wide midwicket

commentPostTextItems.html: 22 run over brings them just 11 short of a white wash
Ball has left the ground and that will not be back, 4th official brings his case out, and as Saturday the ball does get back, at least the 4th official got some excitement and exercise

commentTextItems.html: good line and length delivery, Reza driving, stand and deliver, stands tall and he drags that from the off to long-on
line and length, Reza drives it away full on the off, square drives to cover point, and he is now in a rush
good line and length, Reza drives the ball through the off side, sweetly timed to long-off this time
length but down leg, Reza drives it away to long-on and the crowds wishes are being answered
line and length, Reza drives on the front foot to cover
good length delivery, Hasan drives on the front foot, and at last gets it past the covers, good looking shot does bring him the boundary and worship status from the small crowd

commentTextItems.html: line and length, Hasan drives through the off side but can not find any gaps, he is not going to give his wicket away for anyone
line and length, Hasan drives it away, obliging the crowds requests, but not finding the gap at cover
good line and length, Hasan keeps it out defending towards mid-off, crowd want more than defensive shots, shouting advice from the grass banks
line and length, Hasan pushes forward, firmly defended to mid-off
good line and length, Hasan drives it away, stroking towards mid-off
short of a length and outside the off stump, Reza pulls it away very well, drags that out of the middle of the bat one bounce over the midwicket rope, SHOT

commentPostTextItems.html: That now has woken the crowd up and some noise being generated

dismissalText.commentary: Tushar Imran run out (Otieno) 2 (13b 0x4 0x6) SR: 15.38

dismissalComment.html: What a comedy, Hassan defends to the off, Imran comes, Hassan hesitates, then tries to get back, Imran passes him, keeper diving underhands the ball into the stumps, both batsman are out of the crease, ball is picked up and returned to the bowler who flicks the bails off, again both are still standing in the middle of the wicket, TV umpire takes long to decide Imran is out with the keepers throw
